  "markdown": "[Skip to main content](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n[![Rigetti](https://docs.rigetti.com/img/rigetti.png)](https://docs.rigetti.com/)[QCS](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/)[Integration](https://docs.rigetti.com/integration/)\n[QCS Console](https://qcs.rigetti.com)\n`ctrl``K`\n  * [Welcome to Quantum Cloud Services](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/)\n  * [Getting Started](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/getting-started/)\n  * [Guides](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/)\n    * [Access a QPU](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/access-a-qpu/)\n    * [Benchmarking and Fidelity](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/benchmarking-and-fidelity)\n    * [QCS Group Accounts](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/group-accounts)\n    * [How Programs Are Built & Run](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-programs-are-built-and-run/)\n    * [How to Use Rigetti QPUs](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus)\n    * [Interactive Tutorials](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/interactive-tutorials)\n    * [QCS Credentials](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/qcs-credentials)\n    * [QPU vs. Simulator (QVM)](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/qpus-vs-qvms)\n    * [Quil](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/quil/)\n    * [The Lifecycle of a Program](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/the-lifecycle-of-a-program)\n    * [The Rigetti QCS API](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/the-rigetti-qcs-api)\n    * [Using the QCS CLI](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/using-the-qcs-cli/)\n  * [References](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/references/)\n  * [Troubleshooting](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/troubleshooting/)\n  * [Glossary](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/glossary)\n  * [FAQ](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/faq)\n\n\n  * [](https://docs.rigetti.com/)\n  * [Guides](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/)\n  * How to Use Rigetti QPUs\n\n\nOn this page\n# How to Use Rigetti QPUs\n## Direct: Quantum Cloud Services[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#direct-quantum-cloud-services \"Direct link to Direct: Quantum Cloud Services\")\nRigetti Quantum Cloud Services (QCS) is a quantum-first cloud computing platform. We tightly integrate our QPUs with classical compute hardware and provide access to you through the cloud.\nQCS is the most direct way to work on Rigetti QPUs. With your QCS account, you get access to your own personal cloud-based JupyterLab IDE with the Quil SDK for building and executing Quantum Programs.\nYou can request access to QCS by filling out [this form](https://www.rigetti.com/get-quantum).\n## Partners[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#partners \"Direct link to Partners\")\nRigetti also vends access to our QPUs through several partners, each of which offers its own advantages.\nYou don't need a QCS account to use Rigetti QPUs via these partners; you'll use an account on their platform instead.\n### Amazon Braket[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#amazon-braket \"Direct link to Amazon Braket\")\nYou can use Rigetti QPUs on [Amazon Braket](https://aws.amazon.com/braket/quantum-computers/rigetti/) via the [Amazon Braket SDK](https://github.com/amazon-braket/amazon-braket-sdk-python).\n### Microsoft Azure Quantum[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#microsoft-azure-quantum \"Direct link to Microsoft Azure Quantum\")\nRigetti is a provider for [Azure Quantum](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/products/quantum). You can submit jobs on-demand using both Quil and QIR. See the documentation for the [Rigetti provider](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/quantum/provider-rigetti?tabs=tabid-pyquil) for more details.\n### Strangeworks[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#strangeworks \"Direct link to Strangeworks\")\nAccess Rigetti QPUs online through the [Strangeworks](https://strangeworks.com/) platform.\n### qBraid[\u200b](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#qbraid \"Direct link to qBraid\")\nAccess Rigetti QPUs through the [qBraid platform](https://account.qbraid.com/signin). You can submit jobs through the [qBraid-SDK](https://docs.qbraid.com/v2/sdk/user-guide/overview) using pyQuil, Qiskit, Cirq, or any other gate-based framework compatible with the qBraid [transpiler](https://docs.qbraid.com/v2/sdk/user-guide/transpiler). Quil programs can also be submitted directly via the [qBraid REST API](https://docs.qbraid.com/v2/api-reference/user-guide/overview).\n[Previous Execution and Request timeouts](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-programs-are-built-and-run/execution-and-request-timeouts)[Next Interactive Tutorials](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/interactive-tutorials)\n  * [Direct: Quantum Cloud Services](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#direct-quantum-cloud-services)\n  * [Partners](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#partners)\n    * [Amazon Braket](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#amazon-braket)\n    * [Microsoft Azure Quantum](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#microsoft-azure-quantum)\n    * [Strangeworks](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#strangeworks)\n    * [qBraid](https://docs.rigetti.com/qcs/guides/how-to-use-rigetti-qpus#qbraid)\n\n\nCopyright \u00a9 2026 Rigetti Computing.\n",
